inn1.comm: Roach bangs it in on a good length and forces Watson on the back foot to defend
drifts on the pads and he shuffles and clips it to the leg side
slants it across the left-hander and Warner doesn't offer a shot
this time Warner decides to chase one that slants across him, a late decision on the shot, he misses it
gets across and defends to the off side
slashed! Roach gets a little predictable with his line, full and wide and shaping away further, reaches forward and slashes wide of point
too short and wide, Watson has to reach out to chase that and carve it over cover, there's a sweeper to pick that up
bowls it straighter to Warner, goes back and defends with soft hands
bowls it a touch shorter, he goes back and defends
big appeal for an lbw! Warner's caught off guard by one that straightened from the middle stump line, skidded and hit his pads but that appeared too high
good length on the off stump and he pushes it to mid-off
fullish on the off stump and he pushes it towards mid-off
comes on a bit slower and he ends up chopping it to the off side
a bit straighter this time and he clips it towards square leg
bowls from wide of the crease and angles it inwards, he gets well forward and defends
with Roach's pace you don't have to hit it too hard, short and wide, too wide in fact, Watson rides the pace and carves it over square third man
he bowls it too straight this time, on the pads and fuller and he turns the face of the bat and clips it wide of midwicket
gets across and defends
chance! Late movement off the pitch and Warner tries to loft but spoons it in the air and it just beats mid-off's reach as he runs backwards
short and wide and Warner goes back and plays a controlled slash over backward point, punishes a poor ball
stays at the crease and clips it softly towards midwicket
gets across and pushes it firmly towards mid-off
works this wide of midwicket for a single
Bravo struggles with his line and he sprays it wide down the leg side
reaches out to a wide one and dabs it down to third man
full and wide outside the off stump and he chops it down to point where Pollard stops it
gets well forward and drives to the off side
skids through and he ends up chopping towards the slips
a touch too wide and he dabs it down to third man
short and wide and Warner slashes uppishly wide of point but Samuels is there at sweeper cover to cut it off
Watson shaped to drive straighter but ended up getting an inside edge to square leg
on the pads and he clips it towards square leg
close call for Watson as he goes forward and the ball rises up and nearly shaves the face of the bat
a bit too short from Bravo, Watson goes back and punches it wide of cover, it was in the air but wide of the fielders
Bravo overcompensates by bowling it too full and straight, he clips it away in front of his pads and works it wide of midwicket, Russell dives in vain at the boundary
plonks forward and defends
Warner was unsure of his off stump and nearly nicked that to the keeper, Roach gets it to move away late
he pushes it towards cover point
bangs it in short, Warner plays one of his favourite shots - the pull over square leg, poor length from Roach
Warner once again chases one that slants across him, that swerved away after pitching, close to the edge
gets across and pushes it down towards cover
on the pads and he clips it wide of midwicket for a couple
he clips it softly towards mid-on
fullish on middle and he works it wide of midwicket
spins away late and he ensures he gets behind the line to defend
lunges forward and he pushes it to the off side
tossed up on middle and leg and he pushes it to mid-on
good over from Narine, Watson taps it towards point
nice and straight, Warner goes back and defends
full outside off and it should have been stopped by Roach at mid-off, misfield allows a single
short and wide outside the off stump and he cuts wide of point, Russell does well to run across and mop up
bowls it straight on middle and Watson gets well forward to defend
tries to steer it wide of point but can't beat the infield

Appeal for an lbw and the umpire gives him out but Watson immediately reviews it, big inside edge onto the pads, he was forward to defend, the third umpire takes his time but it was obvious at first glance, Peter Nero's decision has been reversed
gets across and dabs it down to third man
gets forward and clips it to the on side
spins away but he defends solidly
skids away and he opens the face of the bat and dabs it wide of point
goes back and punches it down to cover
not quite short enough to pull, mistimes it to square leg
opens the face of the bat and dabs it down to third man
swings it in late and he clips it behind square for a couple
punches it towards long-off for a single
a bit too full but it doesn't cost him anything, driven straight to mid-off
gives him width and he bends his knee and dabs it to third man
short and wide and he dabs it down to third man
gets on his knee and sweeps but finds square leg
poor delivery, you can't bowl it short to Warner, fetches it from outside off and he pulls wide of Samuels at mid-on
like an action replay, wasn't as short but there was a bit of width, he pulls even wider of mid-on
pulls firmly again and it goes to the same area but Samuels is pushed back to the boundary
stays back and punches it to mid-on

appeal for a catch at slip but the bowler and umpire weren't so sure, spins away from middle and leg and the ball appeared to clip his pad and go to first slip, the catcher and keeper thought they had him
gives him width again and  he cuts wide of point
goes back and punches it back to the bowler
squares him up a bit with the middle stump line, he softly clips it back to the bowler
tries to pull on one leg but the ball hurries on him and deflects off his thigh to the leg side
slower ball on the pads and he tries to whip it away but can't beat midwicket
gets across and chops it down to point
that's massive! Bravo errs by dropping it too short, at this pace Warner has time to read the length and club it over deep midwicket
goes back at the crease and knocks it softly to the on side
goes back at the crease and clips it to square leg
slower delivery on the off stump and he defends
gets well forward and defends towards cover
slides it on the pads and he clips it behind square on the on side
fuller delivery outside off and he drives to the off side
gets forward and steers it towards point
good length on the stumps and he defends again
drifts on the pads and he shuffles and works it down to square leg
strays wide of the leg stump and wide called
on the pads and he works it down to square leg
short and wide and he chops it wide of point, Charles slides and cuts it off
goes back at the crease and punches it back to the bowler
can't get wickets if he bowls wide and short, Warner rocks back and punches it in front of square, wide of cover and it races it away
a bit short again but he goes back and pulls down to long-on
comes well forward and defends to the off side
comes forward and gets an inside edge to the pads
the leg stump line and it bushes his leg and rolls past the keeper
fullish delivery on the stumps and he mistimes the drive to cover
bowls it straight and tucks him up for room, he mistimes it back to the bowler
stays back and punches it towards mid-off
drifts on the pads and he clips him towards midwicket for his fifty
drifts on the pads and he softly works it down to mid-on
streaky! Warner wants to drive it through the off side but gets an inside edge that sneaks past the stumps and down to fine leg
Watson goes back on off and dabs past slip to short third man
tossed up outside the left-hander's off stump and he plays over the ball with an attempted sweep shot
slightly back of a length and nudged to midwicket
flighted, on the stumps and Warner goes down on one knee to leather a flat slog-sweep over midwicket
Narine drops his length back and is pulled fiercely to deep square - but some good fielding from Kieron Pollard keeps the damage down to one

tossed up and smashed out to wide long-on ... where Russell takes a sensational one-handed catch as he leaps over the boundary rope before slam-dunking it back into play before he landed! Great work in the deep, reminiscent of a similar effort by Doherty earlier in the series
width outside off and slapped baseball-style through extra-cover. Warner is cruising here
outside leg stump and nudged off the hips to deep square
orthodox line to the right-hander, pushed off the hips
keeper up the wicket ... back of a length, cut to cover
over the wicket now, Warner drives and inside-edges to short leg
length, outside off, Watson goes back and across and deflects the ball down to third man
length ball, spinning back in past the bat, into the front pad - but Watson was outside the line
tossed up on the stumps and heaved out towards deep midwicket, where it evades a diving fielder before bouncing over the rope
dragged short and pulled through midwicket
more punishment for Narine, who is driven viciously through the covers for another boundary - too full in his length and Warner put it away

but revenge is a swift as it is sweet! Narine gets his man! This one was just held back a little, Warner suffered a rush of blood to the head and swatted in ungainly fashion across the line, only to loop a thick top edge to short third man. A victim of his own success there, Warner, but credit to Narine for continuing to toss it up
length, outside off and going straight on, defended on the back foot
length, on the legs, turned away behind square
pulls it back a touch in length, Forrest puts his hands in the air (like he just don't care) and lets it by
again probes outside off, left alone by the batsman
length ball, not much room outside off and Forrest doesn't quite have room to cut, bottom-edging the ball in the ground
pitched up a bit more, batsman steps out and plays a studied leave
on the stumps, comes forward and plays to midwicket
length, spinning back in from outside off, past the bat and into Watson's midriff, before dropping to safety
tossed up, worked off his legs to short midwicket
full, outside off and Watson smothers the ball with a forward defensive
drifts down the leg side but the batsman can't beat the fielder at square leg with a clip
touch short from Narine and he is deftly cut past short third man for a couple
on the stumps, worked down the ground to long-on - and that's fifty for Watson, his first of the series
full, on the legs, fiddled out to deep backward square
length ball, outside off, Forrest squares up and steers the ball to third man
outside off, drifting in, worked off the pads to long leg
back of a length, Forrest punches to mid-on and scampers through for a single
gets a bit of bounce off the wicket, defended out towards cover on the back foot
pitched up, Watson steps out and clips aerially over midwicket
length ball, steps out and nudges to midwicket
drops short outside off, Watson is quickly back and on the hook, slightly mistimed but it lands short of long-on
tossed up, clipped to deep backward square
length, spinning in from well outside off, dragged down to midwicket
full toss, driven to long-on
length ball, Forrest shows it the maker's name
short ball, Watson doesn't quite get hold of the attempted hook and it dobbles through midwicket
strays too far down leg and is picked off with a neat glance down to fine leg
length, on leg stump, punched short of deep midwicket, though Pollard's arm makes them work hard for two
bouncer, Forrest ducks, though he needn't of bothered - wide on height
short delivery cut hard to point ... and Sammy throws down the non-striker's end. The crowd erupts - but Watson was comfortably home
pitched up and driven to mid-off. Forrest's "Yes" is followed swiftly by "No! No! No!" and Watson this time has to dive to make his ground, though the throw missed
length, on the stumps and defended
full, flighted in towards off, defended on the walk back to the bowler
driven down the ground to long-on
back of a length, flicked of the hips for one
drifting down leg and again worked to deep backward square
on the stumps and turned back to the bowler

nicely flighted from Samuels, tossed up and skidding on past Forrest's outside edge. Baugh takes off the bails and there's a brief review while they check if the batsman's back foot was grounded. It was
rolled out of the hand, clipped to midwicket
drops short and again veering down leg, scooped off the hips in the air through backward square leg - and Pollard's dive along the rope can't prevent a boundary
on the stumps, comes forward and nudges into the leg side
length, better line and Forrest again defends into the on side from in front of his wicket
line and length outside off, forward defensive rolls to cover
slightly shorter, on the stumps, prodded back to the bowler
tossed up on leg and flicked away to deep square
length, outside off and chopped back to the bowler
on the stumps, turned to micwicket
flighted, driven down the ground
tossed up outside off and driven to cover
full, off-stump line, driven to long-off
length, outside off and defended on the back foot
similar line, angled in and turned to short midwicket
full, drifting towards off stump, punched down the ground
short ball, directed at the top of Forrest's head but he swivels and top-edges for a four down to the unguarded boundary at fine leg
length, outside off, driven to the sweeper on the cover boundary
more width outside off, Watson swings through a cut which beats point on the bounce
tossed up, driven to cover
length, on the stumps, defended back to the bowler
picked up from just outside off and driven down the ground
on the stumps, bit of bounce and Forrest edges to short third man trying to turn the ball to leg
driven down the ground to long-off
flighted outside off, punched to long-off again

and now they have one! Russell rolled a bouncer out of his hand and Watson opened the face and guided it to third man like it was on a string. There just wasn't enough pace on it to go all the way ... and Watson, like Warner, fails to go on
pitched up, outside off, whipped through square leg and Bailey is off the mark
pushed to cover on the back foot ... but Sammy's shy at the non-striker's end concedes a run
leg-stump bouncer that veers even further in the air and Carlton Baugh channels Peter Schmeichel to fingertip the ball round the post/prevent a boundary
dropped short on the off side and Russell hits the stumps after fielding in his follow-through. He's quite the athlete, this guy
back of a length, on the stumps, Bailey plays back, patting the to short midwicket
tossed up, driven between mid-on and midwicket
flighted in towards the stumps from wide of the crease, driven to mid-off
length ball, dabbed into the off side
full, Forrest picks it up quickly and crashes a cover drive to the boundary
steady line and length outside off, steered to short third man
on the stumps, pushed to midwicket
flings a loosener down the leg side, which Bailey can't get anything on
slower ball, tossed up outside off, clipped in the air through midwicket, the bat turning in Bailey's hands
slightly back of a length, cut to point
draws the batsman across outside off, dropped short just off the wicket for a quick single
full length, Bailey shuffles across and shovels off his legs
short and wide, cut hard to deep backward point where Johnson Charles saves a couple with a diving stop
length ball, in the corridor outside off, blocked back to the bowler
goes back and stabs it back to the bowler
gets forward and pushes it back to the bowler
gets forward and drives to the off side
comes well forward and pushes it towards extra cover
gets a leading edge that lobs in front of point
gets forward to defend and he's beaten
moves across and pushes it down to mid-on
mistimes the punch towards point
excellent shot, Bailey creates an opportunity for a boundary, he knew there was no slip, delicately dabbed it down to third man, the fielder was a bit square
bowls it straighter and he goes back and defends to the on side
drifts wide down the leg side, tries to flick it away
stabs it down to long-on for a quick single
good slower ball, he tries to flick it away but the ball hits his thigh and nearly dribbles back to the stumps
and there's a boundary straightaway, fires it down the leg side and he gets on his knee early and sweeps to fine leg
pushes it quicker, he tries to flick but misses
fires in a yorker and he fails to squirt it out
another yorker and he jams it hard on the pitch and lobs to the bowler
works another full delivery down to mid-on
he opens the face of the bat and steers it to short third man
short and wide and he fails to put that away, ends up chopping it down to point
gives him width and he tries to cut and nearly squeezes it past the gap between point and cover, the fielder gets a hand to it
he opens the face of the bat and runs it down to third man
Roach gets a wicket off a full toss, lucky break for the West Indies, Roach angles it in, Bailey tries to clear the infield off a low full toss, can't beat Russell at mid-on, easily taken
gets a quick one on the body and he uneasily fends it off to the on side
gets beside the line and steers it to point
fires it full again and he jams it back to the bowler
gets his high backlift down and thuds it to long-off
drifts on the body and he clips it down to short fine leg
another full toss but no second time lucky for West Indies as he slaps it down to long-on
poor line from Samuels, drifts down the leg side and Forrest gets enough bat to beat short fine  leg
tries to work it away to the leg side but the ball clips his pad and rolls to the off side
makes room and tries to slog him away but he swishes at thin air
Lee welcomes the resumption with a boundary, makes room and crashes a length ball over mid-on, not the length to bowl to a pinch-hitter
Lee makes room to a delivery from round the wicket, beaten for pace and bounce, fails to make contact
Roach errs by bowling length again from round the wicket, Lee backs away and swings and gets an outside edge that clears the keeper, one bounce and four
aims for the body and Lee backs away and clips it to the on side
fuller delivery and he knocks it to the off side
comes well forward and punches it back to the bowler

through the gate! Looked like the off cutter, landed on middle and turned in slightly, clipped the pad and hit the stumps, Lee left a big gap between bat and pad, Roach ran across to congratulate Narine and he ran quite close to Lee
full outside the off stump and driven to sweeper cover
shuffles a long way across and works it with the turn to fine leg
turns and bounces, Hussey's forced on the back foot and he stabs at it
drifts on the pads and he shuffles and works it with the angle down to deep midwicket
angles across the left-hander and he opens the face and steers it down to third man
fires it on middle and he works it with the angle to the deep again
shuffles and knocks it to the leg side
Forrest goes on the back foot and clips it to the on side again, he's picking the singles there
forces Hussey on the back foot, he steers it to the off side but can't pinch a single
makes room and steers it towards third man
tosses it full on the pads and he gently works it wide of midwicket
gets well forward and drives towards cover
Hussey goes across his stumps and tries to paddle sweep but the ball spins away and knocks him on the body
drives towards cover for a single
goes back and punches it towards sweeper cover
goes back at the crease and knocks it down to midwicket
drops it short,  Hussey swivels at the crease and pulls it hard along the ground behind square, he picked a huge gap there
goes back at the crease and steers him down to third man
quick low full toss and he punches it down to long-on and that's his half-century
drifts wide down the leg side and he tries to flick it away
fires it full on the pads and he gets across and whips it towards midwicket
full and wide outside the off stump and he smashes it straight to cover, direct hit at the bowler's end but the batsman times his dive well
sharp turn for Narine, Forrest stays back and just about manages to knock it to the on side
steers it to point and takes a quick single
gets to the pitch of the ball and strikes it to long-on
on the pads and he works it to the on side
goes back at the crease and pulls him down to midwicket
gets forward and drives down to sweeper cover
he's not afraid of pitching it a bit short to Hussey, swivels and pulls in front of square straight to the sweeper
the bowling change works for West Indies, Russell bowls a length ball which rises, short enough to pull but Forrest ends up placing it straight to Roach at midwicket

and Russell is on a hat-trick! He gets David Hussey with a snorter, short delivery which fizzes past the batsman and forces him to weave backwards, Hussey tries to upper cut him over third man but the ball hits the face of the bat and the keeper takes it easily
Wade nudges the hat-trick ball down to third man, there were two slips in place
short again and he swivels and pulls him to deep midwicket
another gentle nudge down to third man, he beats the diving slip fielder
fires it wide down the leg side, fails to get bat on it
gets forward and pushes it to the off side
opens the face of the bat and steers it to third man
angles it across him and he punches it down to point
fires it on the pads and he works it down to deep square leg
inside edge to the on side and he scampers the single
another inside edge and Hussey nearly drags it on to his stumps
bangs it in short and he weaves out of that fizzer, well bowled again
steers it to the off side and he pinches a quick single, the fielder didn't gather it quickly enough
drops it with soft hands to the off side and Russell did well to run across the pitch and pick up, the throw was wide of the stumps though and beat the keeper
Russell falls over as he delivers, the batsman works it to the on side
fires it on the pads and he works it down to square leg
angles it across the left-hander and he works it down to third man, Australia need boundaries
fullish on the pads and he works it to the on side
full on the stumps and he works it wide of midwicket
thats a good yorker, manages to dig it out
jams a full delivery down to long-on
he muscles it down to long-on for a single
that's an appeal for a stumping,  Hussey was well forward and was beaten, manages to drag his foot back, the third umpire takes a look
makes room and Wade slashes and gets an outside edge that races to third man
bangs it in short and Wade swivels and clubs it just over Pollard's reach at deep square leg, just enough elevation
add 6 more! Australia are finally pushing on here, Wade makes room to a shortish delivery and slaps it to the roof at the deep cover boundary, the ball's lost
swings and the ball hits his bat and then his helmet, they take a single
the nightmare gets worse for Russell, he sprays this one full and wide and Hussey makes enough room to thud that wide of deep cover
Russell has something to shout about after the hammering, change of pace, slower ball, Hussey makes room and tries to clear deep midwicket but Pollard's there
McKay makes room but Roach is too quick for him, he ends up pushing it softly back to the bowler
McKay makes a lot of room to swing a short delivery over the on side, didn't time it well and the ball swirled to deep midwicket, Darren Bravo ran forward to take the catch
Wade tries to get cheeky and plays a reverse paddle but fails to make contact

Bravo takes another! This time just inches off the ground, Wade makes room and tries to slap it over deep cover, the ball dips to Bravo and he gets his fingers underneath it even as his hands were touching the turf
a run at last! Doherty swings and mistimes the pull to long-on
makes room and swings and they scramble a bye, Baugh's throw is to the bowler, Roach breaks the stumps but he's in

inn2.comm: pitched up and swinging away, Charles barely acknowledges its passing through to the keeper
again nice and full, outside off and moving away, same response from the batsman
line and length, this one doesn't swing, Charles steps across and shoulder arms
length, on the stumps this time and Charles gets an edge on to his pads trying to whip to leg

got him! Charles plays an unconvincing swipe and loops a return catch off the splice of the bat. The ball was short and arrived quicker than he expected as he tried to hook. The St Lucian is out and West Indies' hopes take an early knock
length ball, defended on the back foot outside off
angled across and drifting down the leg side
right line from Hilfenhaus, touch of swing away from the right-hander and Barath leaves
Hilfenhaus repeats the trick and the batsman leaves again
length, outside off, played into the covers
straight - too straight - and Barath clumps a shot off his legs to the square boundary
defended on the back foot outside off
slightly back of a length, outside off, inside-edge off a cut pings past the wicket to short leg

Lee strikes again! Pitched on a good length, the ball rose sharply and brushed Samuel's glove on its way through. That was a devilish delivery and already West Indies are behind the eight ball! Samuels fails again, though he couldn't do much to get out the way of that one
length, angled across the left-hander and defended
straighter line, attacking the stumps, Bravo gets in line and defends solidly
length, drifting across then seaming back a touch, left by the batsman
quick and bouncy, almost wicket to wicket, defended on the back foot towards cover-point
beauty of a delivery, slightly full, enticing Bravo forwards and then seaming away, blowing kisses at the outside edge of the bat on its way past
bumper from Hilfenhaus, slammed in short and directed at the batsman - Barath drops the hands and takes evasive action
length, in the corridor outside off, defended

a shocker from Hilfenhaus, who delivers the ball about five yards down the pitch - it bounces several times then rolls off the cut strip but is called dead ball, rather than wide. Barath defends the follow-up
leg-stump line and clipped to deep backward square
angled across, defended out to point
down the leg side, wrong line to the lefty
length, touch of movement back in as Bravo leaves
length, defended on the back foot outside off
on the stumps, nudged into the leg side
shorter ball, wide and swinging further - Barath attempts to uppercut but can't lay bat on it
straighter line of attack, goes back and across to defend towards mid-on
length ball, off-stump line and nipping back a little, edged into the leg side as Barath pushes forward
back of a length, left as the ball swings away from outside off
on the legs, clipped square but straight to the fielder
back of a length, defended on the back foot in front of the stumps
length ball, angled across outside off and pushed to cover
drops short, targeting the batsman's ribs, jabbed short on the leg side
teasing length, drifting across Bravo, who stands back and swishes in the wind
off-stump line, driven to cover
pacy, line and length outside off, Barath hops back and dabs to point
length delivery, on off stump and Barath shows it the full face of the bat in defence
runs, at last! Lee drops short and wide and Barath opens his arms to club a cut short high over point. Is that the end of the hoodoo?
back on that off-stump line, blocked on the back foot
he goes again, picking up a full-length delivery and chipping it over mid-off. It connected near the bottom of the bat but there was enough power to carry it to the rope
full, on the legs, clipped to midwicket
back of a length and cut, via a top edge down to third man
defended in front of the stumps
drops short and swung meatily over square leg, not the cleanest connection again but it beats the chasing fielder's dive to reach the boundary
on the stumps, slightly back of a length delivery that Barath pushes into a gap at midwicket
pitched up outside off, Bravo smacks a golf-style cover drive straight at the fielder
on the legs and flicked wristily to midwicket where Mike Hussey makes a diving stop
medium pace, on a length outside off, Barath watches it through
back of a length, angled in, punched short towards midwicket and the batsmen decide against running
Barath leans out and defends a length ball to cover
too wide from McKay and he's not quick enough to get away with it ... Barath swings heartily through it, spanking a cut over point for four
tighter line and the batsman lets this one go through to the keeper
back of a length ball, wide of off but swinging back and Barath raises his arms to leave
ambles in, length ball outside off, punched to point off the back foot
slanted across the left-hander, slashed via a thickish edge to third man
banged in on the batsman's body, dropped short on the leg side and Bravo, at the non-striker's end, declines a run
good length, defended square outside off stump
high arm action, tight line, Barath hops back and defends
line drifts across to the leg side and the batsmen nick a leg bye as the run dribbles away off the pad
length delivery left alone outside off stump
pushed through outside off, again Barath's not biting
maintains that line and length, Barath defends into the off side
pitched up a little more and Barath whips his hands through, doesn't middle the drive and it runs to mid-off
shorter delivery, outside off but Barath swivels like a ballerina and hammers a hook shot over midwicket for a one-bounce four
fuller length, driven in the air this time, over cover to the sweeper in the deep
length, defended on the back foot in front of off stump
banged in short and climbing like King Kong up the Empire State to be called wide on height
taken from outside off and steered past the diving point fielder for a couple
length ball, driven square into the off side on the back foot
on the stumps, studied defensive shot from Barath, whose playing very nicely now
leg-stump line and eased around the corner
length ball, guided from just outside off down to third man
angled across Bravo, driven to mid-off

he's gone, feathering through to the keeper! Bravo's struggles had been masked by the giddy hitting at the other end but, after scratching around for 20 deliveries, Bravo attempted another glide to third man and nicked off. He's out of there and West Indies slide further into trouble ...
beaten outside off, fencing at one as he played back
length, seaming back towards the batsman, Bravo lifts his bat high into the air
fuller, straighter ball and Bravo is more comfortable with that, punching the ball off his legs in front of midwicket and the ball scuttles away to the rope
back of a length, nudged square on the leg side
length, outside off, Bravo plays forward with bat and pad, pushing the ball out to point
angled into the right-hander, worked towards midwicket
pitched up a touch, Bravo steps outside the line of off and checks a drive to mid-on coming in from the edge of the circle
back of a length this time, dropped towards cover
on the stumps, touch short, flipped off the hips through midwicket for one
good length outside off, Barath pushes forwards and gets an inside edge to square leg
nagging line and length outside off, deflected to third man with soft hands pressing forward
squeezed away square on the leg side from outside off as Bravo edges across and closes the face
length, pushed into the off side
on the stumps and worked to short midwicket
slower delivery, well outside off and Bravo holds the pose, bat the air, as it trundles through
short and wide, spanked dismissively through point, with Robo Cricketer Mike Hussey running round to make a smart stop in the deep
touch short, on the batsman's body, jabbed away to square leg hopping back by Barath
on the legs, flicked away ... but directed straight to short fine leg, who prevents a run
pitched up outside off, driven with flourish but well stopped by George Bailey at short extra-cover, preventing further damage
shorter, pushed towards cover
angled in towards the stumps, solidly blocked back to the bowler
length ball, popping up and defended by Bravo, the ball dropping on to the wicket between his legs
makes a bit of room and drives down to long-off
tossed up on middle and off and Barath defends
much quicker through the air and he taps it to the on side
Bravo uses his feet and whips it to the on side
gets forward and drives firmly back to the bowler
sprays it wide down the leg side, tries to sweep but misses
just opens the face and steers it towards point
fullish delivery on the pads and he clips it wide of mid-on
gets forward and steers it to the off side
a boundary to break the shackles, pitched up outside the off stump, Bravo leans forward and lofts high over mid-off
goes back at the crease and tucks him to the on side

Watson was delighted with that! Bravo tries to smash another boundary over the off side but ends up punching it straight to Bailey at short extra cover, sharp catch in the end because Bravo really smacked that
comes forward and pushes it back to the bowler
steers it to the off side and they decide against the single
forces a low full toss down to long-on
gets an inside edge onto his boot on  the drive
opens the face of the bat and steers it to backward point
goes back at the crease and punches it down to short extra cover
half-hearted appeal for a caught behind by Wade, he tries to dab it down to third man but the bat hit the pad, good decision by Dharmasena
full delivery on the stumps and he mistimes the drive to mid-off
bowls it straight and tucks him up, he defends
miscued pull and it just lands in front of a diving McKay at mid-on, Barath didn't connect properly
drifts wide down the leg side and wide called
gets forward and thrashes it past cover, the sweeper's there
Pollard gets forward and quietly knocks it back to the bowler
comes forward and pushes it softly towards cover and sets off, good calling
defends towards point and takes a few paces out of his crease, heads back
bowls it flat and straight, not much he could do but defend
Pollard gives the charge and lofts down to long-on, Bailey was at a straight-hit position but Pollard managed to loft it wide of him, quite an unusual field setting
tossed up outside off, he gets forward and defends
gets well forward and defends
hurries on to him, he tries to nudge it away but the ball clips his pads and rolls away
a bit short and he's tucked up for room, opens the face and runs it down to third man
bowls it straight again, good line and Pollard quietly defends it
the stump-to-stump line is stifling Pollard, once again he softly pushes it down the track
shorter delivery on the body and Pollard knocks it to the on side for a quick single
opens the face and runs it down to third man
runs it down towards fine leg
he gets forward and defends towards point
pushes it towards cover

the pressure gets to Barath! Tossed up on the off stump, Barath gets on his knee and tries to slog him away but gets a tame top edge that swirls to the region of mid-on, Bailey gets underneath it and a frustrated Barath walks off
tossed up on the pads and Pollard whips it with intent over a diving midwicket, the fielder was quite close, plenty of power behind that shot
bit risky there, the first slip was wide and yet he steered it just wide of him
gets across and taps it back to the bowler
Hilfenhaus bowls it straight again and Pollard can only clip it back down the pitch
follows that up with a sharp bouncer, Pollard doesn't offer a shot
keeps him on the back foot and he defends back to the bowler
Baugh lunges forward and steers it down towards point
comes well forward and defends again
another forward defense, another dot ball
make that four in a row, Baugh goes back and defends
five dot balls, he stays back and punches it towards point
clips the last delivery to the on side and keeps the strike
tucks him up for room and he pushes it firmly to the packed off-side field
gets half forward and steers it past the gap at cover, Pollard back on strike
stays beside the line and taps it to the off side

drops it to the off side and risks a single, great attempt by Warner to slide and under-arm the ball towards the stumps in one motion, the ball was just wide of the stumps, the batsman was short of his ground
big slash outside off and he misses, no foot movement there
that's more like it, wide outside off and he waits for the ball to come on to him before cutting wide of point
that's the Pollard we know! Tossed up outside off and he stays at the crease and lofts crisply just over the wide long-off fielder
didn't exactly time it as well as he would have liked but it still carried over wide long-on, raw power, he stayed at the crease and slogged
comes over the wicket, bowls it flat and Pollard defends
fires another flat delivery and he taps it back to the bowler
whips it away close to his pads and picks the gap deep on the on side
fullish outside the off stump and driven down to mid-off
wide outside off and Baugh repeats the square cut that fetched him the boundary, Lee is square at third man so he cuts it off
on the pads and he clips it down to short fine leg, the fielder slides and stops it
crisp timing! Baugh picks the big gap wide of cover and plays another neat cut, McKay feeding him width again
punches this firmly to the off side
goes back at the crease and taps it to the leg side
squares him up on the off stump and he gets an outside edge down to third man
tucks him up for room and he pushes it to the off side again
Lee tests him out again by bowling it straight on the stumps, manages to get his bat behind in time
defends in front of the stumps again, it's another quiet over in the making

a collision! Wade unfortunately has hurt himself! Ouch, that will sting. Baugh tried to go for broke over the leg side, not sure where he was aiming but he got a top edge that swirled high down to fine leg, it was Hilfenhaus' catch all the way but Wade ran across from his position, two fielders claiming it, Hilfy managed to hang on despite a rampaging Wade ramming onto him, the catcher's knee hits Wade's stomach and the keeper was down, writhing in pain
pushes it to the off side and Bailey stops it
swinging in on the stumps and he clips it down to midwicket
he beats him outside the off stump, tried to run it down to third man
bangs it in short and he pulls firmly to deep square leg
tucks him up for room and he pushes it to the off side field
leading edge but it's safe of the fielders
beats him outside off, he prods forward but was beaten for pace
teases him with width but Pollard opts to leave it alone
beats him again, he pitches it up a bit more and Pollard was forward and across to drive, not far from the edge
fullish in length outside off and he pushes it wide of cover
fends off a shortish delivery and the ball dribbles towards Wade, they take a quick single and Wade hits the stumps at the other end but they steal an overthrow off the ricochet
squares him up and he gets an outside edge down towards third man

the captain himself gets rid of the danger man! Pollard shuffles a long way across his stumps to whip a full delivery over the on side, it was a flat hit but straight down Mike Hussey's throat at deep midwicket
Russell sees a big gap at wide long-on and slaps a short delivery to that region, West Indies can only play in one gear now
taps it to the off side
firm punch square of the wicket and the point fielder dives and stops it
steered with soft hands down to third man
swing and a miss outside off, no foot movement
low full toss and he gets on his knee and smacks it straight to deep square leg
low full toss and Sammy stays at the crease and has a golf swing, over long-on, raw power
comes forward and drives firmly to the off side
goes back and tries to slash that past point but he doesn't get the placement right
comes forward and drives to cover
fired on the pads and he whips it to the on side
length, outside off, slashed to cover
punched through to covers to the man in the deep
on the body, nurdled short on the leg side but too tight for a run
room outside off, guided with a flick of the wrists down to the third man boundary
full toss, clubbed out to wide long-on
length ball, rising steeply as Russell goes back in his crease and misses out with an attempted cut
length ball, scooped from off stump out to deep midwicket where it bounces 15 yards or so in front of the fielder
pushed to cover for a quick single, the throw from Doherty missing the stumps
fullish length, outside off, Sammy gives himself room and batters a full-blooded swing straight back down the ground for four
pitched up again and driven hard to extra-cover
full toss on the legs, Sammy only has to get a slice of willow on it and it races down to fine leg

my, oh my, Sammy has dumped Lee into the car park over deep midwicket! It was another rank full-bunger and the West Indies captain connected sweetly as he hefted through the on side. Why is he coming in at No. 9?!
length ball, pushed to mid-off
pitched up and Sammy swings murderously through the ball, taking a single out to the cover boundary
wide yorker from Hilfenhaus, steered neatly behind point, using the pace of the ball to send it bowling away to the rope
pitched up, driven to extra-cover and Russell goes tumbling over as his makes it to the non-striker's end
full, outside off, drilled to long-off
pitched up, Russell goes big but doesn't quite connect, the ball trickling back to the bowler
full, wide of off but Sammy has long arms and he drags another meaty swing down the ground - that brings up the 50 partnership, in just 30 balls
dropped? Yes, I think so, though it was a tough caught and bowled chance, as Sammy slashed a full-pitched ball back past McKay, whose outstretched fingers couldn't cling on
full again, dug out down to long-on
another massive heave from Sammy, swinging across the line and sending McKay over wide long-on

that's a monstrous blow and it takes Sammy to the brink of fifty from 19 balls! McKay tried to get it up in the blockhole but Sammy got right underneath it and hammed the ball over deep midwicket. Carnage!
pitched up again and drilled down the ground! The shot bisects long-on and long-off and takes Sammy past 50 from 20 balls, equalling his own West Indian record
and the punishment contiues, Russell smearing a full toss over point and away for four more!
pitched up full and wide, this time Russell can't get his bat on it
yorker-length, dug out to point and they sneak a single
length ball, drilled back to the bowler
superb yorker, Sammy jams his bat down and ends up off his feet due to the momentum
swung hard down the ground but that's just a single to long-on
tossed up, outside off, hacked back to the bowler
slammed down the ground and David Hussey and long-off can only tip it further over the rope as he leaps in the air desperately
turned off the stumps through midwicket
flighted up and missed with a swipe outside off
chipped back over the bowler's head but reeled in at long-off
on the stumps, driven back to the bowler
length, tucked into the leg side
slower ball, short and wide, rocks back and cuts through point
full-pitched delivery on leg stump, punched down the ground
picked up outside off and boomed back down the ground, beating Warner at long-off - that's a new West Indies record for the eighth wicket
full on the leg side and deftly clipped behind backward square for another boundary. Russell is emulating Sammy now!
pitched up again - as if it matters - and driven to long-off
too full and slashed hard through point. The water is no longer falling from the sky but it's raining runs and Australia are being swamped!
pushed through a bit quicker, nudged to cover
tossed up, driven down the ground for one
flighted, steps back and creamed wide of long-off - they get back for two and that brings up the hundred partnership!
length, on the stumps, Russell goes for a slog-sweep and is hit on the body

forward press on the stumps, Australia appeal for lbw - they're going to review it. The question is whether it was bat or pad first ... the side camera angle suggests pad, and the ball was going on to hit ... Russell is gone and Doherty has claimed a potentially crucial wicket! Russell goes for a rapid 41, ending a century stand that brought West Indies back from the dead. Surely that's the final blow, though ...?
length, nudged into the leg side. Have the bowlers decided that pitching it up is no longer the plan?
length delivery, angling in, driven past extra-cover for a single to bring Sammy back on strike
back of a length outside off, Sammy ticks it to square leg
back around the wicket ... thick edge but it flies through the vacant first slip area, past Wade's acrobatic lunge
back of a length, Narine has a swish with the bat well away from his body but misses
short again, cramping the batsman, who fences uncertainly - that's another precious dot for McKay and Australia
tossed up, Sammy works it to point but doesn't try for a run
picked up from a fullish length and humped down the ground, they take on the fielder's arm and get two
flatter delivery, Sammy cuts hard to the cover boundary
drifted across the left-hander, beating the outside edge and drawing excited noises from Wade
length, outside off, pushed to cover
on the stumps, dragged down a touch, defended on the to wicket
pitched up from McKay, on the legs and Sammy misses out, the ball hitting the pad and remaining on the cut strip. The batsman shakes his fist in frustration
full length, driven out past cover this time, again Sammy unable to get underneath it
length, on the stumps, Narine steps away and swings his arms through a drive that skitters to mid-off and there's no run
slightly short, outside off but pulled over the on side, into the vacant deep midwicket area, with deep square leg running around to field

takes the pace off it and Wade takes a skier to leave West Indies nine down! Narine was aiming to hit over the leg side again, but was through the shot too quickly, spooning up and down and out. While Sammy's out there, Australia fans won't unclench, though ...
short, scraped away through point
pacy yorker, dug out into the off side
room outside off for Sammy to swing, they get a single after a misfield at cover
aimed right up into the slot, but sliding down leg, flicking the pad on the way through to Wade, who can't cling on anyway
well-directed bouncer from Lee and the batsman ducks under it as it veers down the leg side - not called wide though
length, targeting the stumps, Roach squeezes a single out to deep backward square leg
pitched up and Sammy squirts the ball out to third man to retain the strike
slower ball, on the stumps and dinked back to the bowler, unable to make anything of it
drifts on to the legs and Sammy times the ball to the deep backward square boundary. The flame flickers
length ball, clipped through the infield to the cover boundary
line and length from Watson, Roach gets behind the ball and defends to cover
draws Roach outside off, length ball pushed square on the off side. "No!" yells Sammy
slings one down the leg side - a freebie for West Indies
outside off, defended back to the bowler
length ball, goes for a big ole swing of the arms but fails to connect
pitched up and shovelled out to deep midwicket but there's a man there and they can only take one
length, targeting the stumps, Roach gets across and nudges into the leg side
he goes again, another six! Play it again, Sammy! Lee sent down a slow bouncer but Sammy read it, stayed back in the crease and hoicked the ball over deep square leg
pitched up this time and Sammy gets right behind it to block
full, almost yorker-length, slanted into the batsman, dug out towards deep midwicket and a superb stop prevents it going for four ... Sammy keeps the strike, though
full, right in the blockhole, Sammy digs it out, it squirms past the bowler but they decide not to take a single

full, heaved away into the leg side once again ... but this time he finds a fielder. Sammy perishes in the deep and West Indies suffer heroic defeat! He swung hard but this time without quite the same venom, looping a high catch to Mike Hussey at deep square leg. A valiant innings from the captain but his side fall short
